text: When the Senate returns on Monday, Feb. 26, we will continue our work to confirm the president’s nominees, including voting on Lisa Branch of GA for the 11th U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals and Tripp Self of GA for the U.S. District Court for the Middle District of Georgia.
Happy birthday @repjohnlewis !
Congratulations to silver medalist @eamslider24 in women's bobsled! We are very proud of Douglasville, GA,-native Elana Meyers Taylor's achievements and dedication! #TeamUSA
Saddened to learn of the passing of Billy Graham, but thankful for the life of this leader whose faith and service to the Lord touched an untold number of lives.

I am proud that the state of Georgia is being represented by two remarkable athletes in the @USBSF bobsled team at the #2018Olympics. Please join me in wishing @Chrisak4298 from Stockbridge and @eamslider24 from Douglasville the very best of luck as they go for gold next week!

Margaret Weichert is a seasoned professional who will provide excellent leadership at the @WhiteHouse Office of Management and Budget. Congratulations to this fine Georgian on her Senate confirmation last evening.

Two of our #2018WinterOlympics athletes are from Georgia! Both Chris Kinney from Stockbridge, and @eamslider24 from Douglasville, are members of the @USBSF bobsled team. We wish them the very best as they compete later this month!
This week, @POTUS stood up for American jobs by stopping unfair and opaque financial practices by Qatar. To ensure fair competition the UAE needs to follow the rules of #OpenSkies as well.

I applaud @StateDept, @POTUS for maintaining our Open Skies agreement with Qatar while correcting the lack of financial transparency in order to create a level playing field for American workers. #OpenSkies

It's #BlackHistoryMonth, a time when we honor the accomplishments and contributions of black Americans throughout history. Please join me in celebrating the diversity that the African American people and culture have brought to the state of Georgia and to our nation.

I’m a cosponsor of S.2311, the “Pain-Capable Unborn Child Protection Act,” along with 45 other senators. Today’s vote will allow us to consider this important legislation on the Senate floor. I urge my colleagues to support life.
